The paper deals with community detection, which is a problem in machine learning and graph theory. The use of side information to improve the exact recovery phase transition is a common theme in machine learning, which suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The stochastic block model is a popular model for community detection, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) sub-category. The use of side information also suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-category. The paper also involves information theory, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-category. Finally, the use of algorithms and procedures for community detection suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category.
